genresAdvancedInfo.name: seggae
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A music genre that emerged in the 1980s in Mauritius, blending Sega and reggae music. Seggae is characterized by its use of Sega rhythms with reggae beats, basslines, and guitar riffs. The lyrics often address social and political issues, as well as everyday struggles and hardships. Seggae has become a popular and influential music genre in Mauritius and has also gained a following in other parts of the world.
